WEBVTT

00:02.089 --> 00:03.612
<i>Previously on "Resident Alien"...</i>

00:03.612 --> 00:04.700
Hi, Dad.

00:04.700 --> 00:06.484
This is my sweet
little girl, Iva.

00:06.484 --> 00:07.790
- Hello, sweetheart.
- Hi, Dad.

00:07.790 --> 00:09.009
You know, your mother
and I were talking,

00:09.009 --> 00:10.880
and there's a lot
of very interesting

00:10.880 --> 00:12.055
possibilities in Park City.

00:12.055 --> 00:14.840
<i>I met my mother today.</i>

00:14.840 --> 00:15.885
Can I help you?

00:15.885 --> 00:17.017
Well, how did it go?

00:17.017 --> 00:18.366
D'Arcy.

00:18.366 --> 00:19.497
<i>Do you think
you've been abducted?</i>

00:19.497 --> 00:21.412
How would someone
know for sure?

00:21.412 --> 00:23.893
<i>Some people find
chips that aliens</i>

00:23.893 --> 00:25.634
<i>use as a tracking device.</i>

00:25.634 --> 00:27.940
<i>What brings you
to this neck of the woods?</i>

00:27.940 --> 00:30.769
I'm here to kill my father.

00:30.769 --> 00:31.770
You must know chemistry.

00:31.770 --> 00:33.076
You recognize this formula?

00:33.076 --> 00:35.035
<i>It is a compound
with an alien element.</i>

00:35.035 --> 00:39.169
<i>This formula may be the key to
understanding the Greys' plan.</i>

00:39.169 --> 00:40.214
What is going on?

00:40.214 --> 00:41.519
Why are you being so secretive?

00:41.519 --> 00:43.347
Why are you being
so inquisitive?

00:43.347 --> 00:45.045
You and Liv practically
begged me for a new deputy,

00:45.045 --> 00:47.047
but now he's gone, and you
haven't even replaced him?

00:47.047 --> 00:48.352
No.

00:48.352 --> 00:50.050
<i>I have seen this
in human movies.</i>

00:50.050 --> 00:51.312
<i>I am in love.</i>

00:51.312 --> 00:52.791
<i>You work for the Greys now.</i>

00:52.791 --> 00:56.099
<i>You are gonna help us
get Harry's alien DNA.</i>

00:56.099 --> 00:58.188
Once you give me what I need,
you will leave the planet,

00:58.188 --> 00:59.798
and you will never
see him again.

01:01.148 --> 01:05.108
<i>♪ Oh, to the future</i>

01:05.108 --> 01:09.373
<i>♪ Oh</i>

01:09.373 --> 01:12.115
<i>♪ Look to the future</i>

01:12.115 --> 01:16.119
<i>♪ Know how I feel</i>

01:16.119 --> 01:18.948
<i>♪ Then you can be sure</i>

01:18.948 --> 01:22.386
<i>♪ My love is real</i>

01:22.386 --> 01:25.998
<i>♪ Happiness haven</i>

01:25.998 --> 01:30.133
<i>♪ Waiting for you and me</i>

01:30.133 --> 01:33.919
<i>♪ For you and me</i>

01:44.104 --> 01:47.803
<i>♪ What do you get
when you fall in love? ♪</i>

01:47.803 --> 01:51.111
<i>♪ A guy with a pin
to burst your bubble ♪</i>

01:51.111 --> 01:52.764
This one is dead.

01:52.764 --> 01:54.897
<i>♪ That's what you get
for all your trouble ♪</i>

01:54.897 --> 01:57.334
<i>It is better
to have loved and lost,</i>

01:57.334 --> 02:01.077
<i>said some idiot, who I
hope is also dead now.</i>

02:01.077 --> 02:03.862
<i>Love is like being
shot out of a cannon--</i>

02:03.862 --> 02:06.343
<i>thrilling, except for
that very last part</i>

02:06.343 --> 02:08.476
<i>when you hit the ground
and your body breaks</i>

02:08.476 --> 02:10.739
<i>into tiny pieces.</i>

02:10.739 --> 02:12.654
That part ruins the trip.

02:18.529 --> 02:21.010
<i>♪ Out of those
chains, those chains ♪</i>

02:21.010 --> 02:22.316
You know what
I just realized?

02:22.316 --> 02:24.274
This song has
repeated three times.

02:24.274 --> 02:26.711
And then I asked
myself, who would

02:26.711 --> 02:29.366
be listening to a
1970s heartbreak song

02:29.366 --> 02:31.803
over and over again?

02:31.803 --> 02:34.458
And now, here I am.

02:34.458 --> 02:37.635
This song is the
truest one ever written.

02:37.635 --> 02:39.463
Can you please make it stop?

02:39.463 --> 02:42.292
I'm sorry about Heather,
but we have a lot

02:42.292 --> 02:43.641
of patients this morning.

02:43.641 --> 02:47.167
I do not care whether
they live or die!

02:47.167 --> 02:49.647
Maybe you keep that inside.

02:49.647 --> 02:53.825
And then go home and
finish the bomb, please.

02:53.825 --> 02:56.480
OK, first up,
Mayor Ben for therapy.

02:56.480 --> 03:00.267
I do not care
if Mayor Ben dies.

03:00.267 --> 03:02.225
Well, that makes two of us.

03:02.225 --> 03:03.226
Ha.

03:03.226 --> 03:05.663
He was joking.

03:05.663 --> 03:07.230
I wasn't.

03:41.743 --> 03:44.267
Oh, shit!

03:44.267 --> 03:46.008
Oh.

04:03.460 --> 04:06.333
It's-- it's delicate.

04:06.333 --> 04:09.553
There's this guy
at work that I'm having

04:09.553 --> 04:11.251
a bit of a problem with.

04:11.251 --> 04:13.514
Sheriff Mike.

04:13.514 --> 04:16.256
No, it's not.

04:16.256 --> 04:17.648
If it is not
Sheriff Mike,

04:17.648 --> 04:19.824
then it is Timmy
the sandwich guy.

04:19.824 --> 04:21.565
And if you cannot
get along with him,

04:21.565 --> 04:25.134
then you are a real dick.

04:25.134 --> 04:26.483
OK, it's Mike.

04:26.483 --> 04:28.790
Yeah, he's--
he's up to something.

04:28.790 --> 04:30.095
Hmm.

04:30.095 --> 04:32.663
You know, he's lying
and sneaking around.

04:32.663 --> 04:35.144
And I'm pretty sure the
new deputy he made me hire

04:35.144 --> 04:36.537
is a murderer.

04:36.537 --> 04:38.539
Don't trust anyone.

04:38.539 --> 04:43.326
You can never truly know
how another man feels--

04:43.326 --> 04:47.591
a woman, bird.

04:47.591 --> 04:51.595
You could wake up every
morning next to Sheriff Mike.

04:51.595 --> 04:54.076
He could tell you he
loves you, and you

04:54.076 --> 04:56.470
will never know if he does.

04:56.470 --> 04:59.908
<i>He could caress your face, and
you could hand-feed sunflower</i>

04:59.908 --> 05:01.866
<i>seeds into his
delicate little mouth</i>

05:01.866 --> 05:03.346
<i>while he says he wants
to spend the rest</i>

05:03.346 --> 05:07.481
<i>of his life with you,
but it could all be a lie.</i>

05:07.481 --> 05:11.354
I want to spend
the rest of my life with you.

05:11.354 --> 05:13.704
That could be a lie.

05:15.010 --> 05:17.099
Thank you for that image.

05:17.099 --> 05:21.190
You only have yourself in
this world and no one else.

05:21.190 --> 05:23.497
You owe me $100.

05:25.107 --> 05:26.848
Oh, I see.

05:26.848 --> 05:30.895
You're saying I'm giving Mike
the power in the relationship.

05:30.895 --> 05:34.769
I need to find out what's
going on, take my power back.

05:34.769 --> 05:36.684
I didn't say any of that.

05:36.684 --> 05:39.121
You know,
you have a strange method,

05:39.121 --> 05:40.775
but I'm starting to get it.

05:40.775 --> 05:43.038
You say the wrong thing for
me to learn the right thing.

05:43.038 --> 05:45.345
- Wrong.
- Right.

05:45.345 --> 05:47.999
Great session.

05:47.999 --> 05:50.350
Turn off the light!

05:50.350 --> 05:51.612
Son of a bitch.

05:56.051 --> 05:57.922
Harry, God damn it!

05:57.922 --> 06:01.796
That's it.
I'm pulling the plug.

06:02.710 --> 06:05.321
Not something you want to
hear in a doctor's office.

06:05.321 --> 06:08.498
Hi.

06:08.498 --> 06:10.370
Mary Ellen.

06:10.370 --> 06:12.328
I know.

06:13.677 --> 06:18.290
I wanted to say
sorry for how I was.

06:18.290 --> 06:20.162
I wasn't in the best place.

06:20.162 --> 06:23.339
There was some things going on.

06:23.339 --> 06:25.863
It doesn't matter.

06:25.863 --> 06:29.693
Want to know about your
family, your history?

06:29.693 --> 06:32.653
Maybe we grab some food
and talk?

06:36.134 --> 06:37.788
Um.

06:43.098 --> 06:45.883
Sir, we have a problem.

06:45.883 --> 06:48.669
I did that trick you
taught me about putting

06:48.669 --> 06:50.801
a hair on my lunch bag
in the refrigerator

06:50.801 --> 06:52.847
to see if anyone's touched
it, but with our murder

06:52.847 --> 06:55.110
investigation board,
and they did.

07:01.812 --> 07:03.248
Are you saying
you've been putting

07:03.248 --> 07:05.512
your hair in the refrigerator?

07:05.512 --> 07:08.515
It was your technique.

07:08.515 --> 07:10.734
You said you put
your hair on your--

07:10.734 --> 07:12.867
I said I put
my hair on my lunch.

07:12.867 --> 07:14.608
I didn't say put
your hair on your lunch.

07:14.608 --> 07:16.523
That's unsanitary.

07:16.523 --> 07:19.526
And did you hear the part I
said about our murder board?

07:19.526 --> 07:21.571
I hear everything, deputy.

07:21.571 --> 07:23.573
I'm like a fennec fox.

07:23.573 --> 07:24.618
Look it up.

07:24.618 --> 07:26.271
It's cute as hell.

07:26.271 --> 07:29.536
Well, I'd say the fact that
he's been asking questions

07:29.536 --> 07:33.148
about our movements tells
me that our likely spy

07:33.148 --> 07:35.933
is the mayor.

07:35.933 --> 07:37.979
Plus the fact that he's
spying on us right now.

07:41.678 --> 07:42.679
No, it's fine.

07:42.679 --> 07:44.159
He don't have nothing.

07:44.159 --> 07:45.639
If he asks, we'll just
say that board's part

07:45.639 --> 07:47.945
of a game we're playing,
a murder mystery

07:47.945 --> 07:50.774
called the
"Alien Trackers Van."

07:50.774 --> 07:53.516
Yeah, part of the
"Sheriff Mike's Murder

07:53.516 --> 07:55.126
Mystery Game" series, right?

07:55.126 --> 07:59.261
And the next one is
"Sheriff Mike and the Secret

07:59.261 --> 08:00.915
of the Old Sawmill."

08:00.915 --> 08:01.959
OK.

08:01.959 --> 08:03.874
But on the other
thing, you said

08:03.874 --> 08:06.616
you'd found another chemist we
can talk to about the formula

08:06.616 --> 08:10.315
from Robert's notebook.

08:10.315 --> 08:12.230
You said we.

08:12.230 --> 08:14.232
Are you back on
this thing with me?

08:14.232 --> 08:15.799
Yes, sir.

08:15.799 --> 08:18.280
I don't want to let
being afraid stop

08:18.280 --> 08:20.064
me from doing what's right.

08:20.064 --> 08:23.851
If I can put my nana in the
hospital, I can do anything.

08:23.851 --> 08:24.634
Mm.

08:24.634 --> 08:26.114
How's she doing?

08:26.114 --> 08:27.681
I haven't asked.

08:27.681 --> 08:30.988
Anyway, I have kind of a
crazy plan to catch Joseph.

08:30.988 --> 08:32.816
Yeah, well, whatever
it is, with the mayor

08:32.816 --> 08:37.168
watching us all the time,
it's gonna be a lot harder.

08:41.869 --> 08:43.827
Be a little harder.

08:50.486 --> 08:52.357
Liza?

08:52.357 --> 08:54.534
Hello, Dad.

08:54.534 --> 08:56.623
Hey.

08:56.623 --> 09:01.802
Um, now is not a very
good time for a visit.

09:01.802 --> 09:06.633
Maybe you can come back
when it's warmer outside

09:06.633 --> 09:09.200
and we can throw a ball.

09:09.200 --> 09:12.639
So you want to
send me away again?

09:12.639 --> 09:14.510
No, I did not send
you away the first time.

09:14.510 --> 09:16.512
I put you on a nice bus.

09:16.512 --> 09:19.167
I even gave you my last apple.

09:19.167 --> 09:21.561
You couldn't wait
to get rid of me.

09:21.561 --> 09:24.128
Ah!

09:24.128 --> 09:26.348
Liza, you are
being very naughty.

09:26.348 --> 09:28.611
If you do not stop
throwing knives at Daddy,

09:28.611 --> 09:30.134
I will limit your screen time.

09:30.134 --> 09:31.222
It was freezing there.

09:31.222 --> 09:33.224
You didn't even
pack me a sweater.

09:33.224 --> 09:36.793
Ah!

09:36.793 --> 09:38.534
There's something
different about you.

09:38.534 --> 09:41.319
Ah!

09:41.319 --> 09:42.320
Bridget.

09:42.320 --> 09:44.279
My baby, it's you.

09:44.279 --> 09:45.454
Hey-hey-hey-hey-hey!

09:45.454 --> 09:47.630
I like your new skin.

09:47.630 --> 09:49.371
Augh!

09:49.371 --> 09:50.764
Well, you broke my nose.

09:50.764 --> 09:53.114
- Ah!
- Ooh!

09:53.114 --> 09:55.203
Bridget!
Oh!

09:55.203 --> 09:56.334
So strong now.

09:56.334 --> 09:57.945
My big, strong baby.

09:57.945 --> 10:00.338
And you've learned to
recreate Liza's clothing.

10:00.338 --> 10:01.862
Daddy is so proud.

10:01.862 --> 10:04.952
You're the worst father
ever, and I hate you.

10:04.952 --> 10:07.128
Oh, you want me dead?

10:08.346 --> 10:11.654
OK.

10:11.654 --> 10:13.177
No, not yet.

10:13.177 --> 10:14.526
I have something else
planned for you first,

10:14.526 --> 10:15.615
something worse than death.

10:15.615 --> 10:16.659
What is it?

10:16.659 --> 10:20.228
I guess you'll see.

10:20.228 --> 10:21.577
Hey, you left your--

10:21.577 --> 10:22.665
your hat.

10:22.665 --> 10:25.494
That's a free hat for me.

10:27.670 --> 10:28.845
Ugh.

10:35.896 --> 10:38.159
Oh, hi.

10:41.336 --> 10:42.380
Oh, thank you.

10:42.380 --> 10:45.601
Oh, my god,
I have to pee so bad.

10:45.601 --> 10:48.473
Oh, and notice I didn't ask
why you're cuffed to the bed.

10:48.473 --> 10:50.519
That is something
a mature person would do,

10:50.519 --> 10:51.563
and I want credit.

10:51.563 --> 10:52.913
Yeah, I noticed.

10:52.913 --> 10:54.610
Thanks for that.

10:54.610 --> 10:55.785
It's nothing weird.

10:55.785 --> 10:58.266
It's-- it's not a sex thing.

10:58.266 --> 10:59.659
Actually,
the sex version would

10:59.659 --> 11:01.399
be the not weird explanation.

11:01.399 --> 11:04.576
Well, maybe sometimes
you just love your bed

11:04.576 --> 11:06.491
so much you don't want
to be taken from it.

11:16.806 --> 11:19.026
I mean, honestly, it's-- it's
too crazy to even talk about.

11:19.026 --> 11:22.029
It's-- but I'm fine.

11:22.029 --> 11:27.034
Yeah, right.

11:27.034 --> 11:30.167
I'll just say, you're,
like, the least crazy

11:30.167 --> 11:32.300
person I know in the world.

11:32.300 --> 11:38.306
So maybe whatever's happening
to you, it's not so crazy.

11:40.612 --> 11:42.397
Just stay open.

11:42.397 --> 11:45.052
That's all.

11:45.052 --> 11:47.532
Yeah, yeah.

11:47.532 --> 11:48.925
Sure.

11:50.057 --> 11:51.885
Hey, dickhead!

11:54.191 --> 11:55.976
I need your help.

11:55.976 --> 11:58.674
My baby Bridget is back.

11:58.674 --> 11:59.719
Cool.

11:59.719 --> 12:00.807
You two have fun.

12:00.807 --> 12:02.373
No, no, it is not fun.

12:02.373 --> 12:04.158
He wants me dead.

12:04.158 --> 12:05.725
Sucks to be you.

12:05.725 --> 12:08.118
That's why I need your help.

12:08.118 --> 12:11.252
Hey, it's going
to be exciting, huh?

12:11.252 --> 12:14.777
Two-- two good friends
on an adventure.

12:14.777 --> 12:16.997
You only want my help
because I can see aliens.

12:16.997 --> 12:17.998
What?

12:17.998 --> 12:19.521
You can do that?

12:19.521 --> 12:22.263
What a useful skill
for my good friend to have.

12:22.263 --> 12:23.743
Do you even care
I got grounded

12:23.743 --> 12:25.048
over the science fair?

12:25.048 --> 12:27.355
Because you stole my caldera.

12:27.355 --> 12:29.096
I should be the angry one.

12:29.096 --> 12:30.750
You're lucky I need you.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.360
Yeah, like always.

12:32.360 --> 12:34.231
And after you get
what you need,

12:34.231 --> 12:35.537
it's like I'm not
even alive,

12:35.537 --> 12:39.019
which makes you
the D-I-C-K head.

12:39.019 --> 12:41.064
Fine, where is it?

12:41.064 --> 12:42.326
I know you have it.

12:42.326 --> 12:44.285
Ah, ha-ha.

12:44.285 --> 12:47.201
All right, if you are not going
to help me track an alien,

12:47.201 --> 12:49.420
then you are not
the alien tracker.

12:49.420 --> 12:50.465
Keep it.

12:50.465 --> 12:52.206
I don't care.

12:52.206 --> 12:53.947
I wish you never
came to Patience.

12:55.905 --> 12:59.169
Ah.

12:59.169 --> 13:02.042
So you said you had
information about my family?

13:02.042 --> 13:05.045
I've never really
been a family person.

13:05.045 --> 13:06.916
You know, I didn't
want to spit in a tube

13:06.916 --> 13:10.572
or chase down cousins, but I
know it's different for you.

13:10.572 --> 13:14.141
And I think I have
what you want.

13:17.057 --> 13:19.581
Ah.

13:21.322 --> 13:23.150
Um, is there a problem?

13:23.150 --> 13:25.674
I hate to bring this up,
but getting this together

13:25.674 --> 13:27.763
was a lot of work--

13:27.763 --> 13:31.071
photocopies, phone calls,
two trips to the courthouse,

13:31.071 --> 13:34.988
took the day off work
to drive up here, gas.

13:34.988 --> 13:36.859
I'm saying there are expenses.

13:36.859 --> 13:38.426
They add up.

13:38.426 --> 13:41.124
I bet.

13:41.124 --> 13:42.865
You happen to know how high?

13:42.865 --> 13:44.998
750 bucks.

13:51.178 --> 13:52.744
<i>I had a bad feeling.</i>

13:52.744 --> 13:55.660
<i>I only get bad feelings
about bad people.</i>

13:55.660 --> 13:58.968
<i>And since my job only
puts me with bad people,</i>

13:58.968 --> 14:01.753
<i>I feel bad all the time.</i>

14:02.406 --> 14:03.973
<i>So can you blame
a guy for needing</i>

14:03.973 --> 14:05.714
<i>a drink every now and then?</i>

14:07.368 --> 14:10.545
Hot.

14:10.545 --> 14:12.025
He still there?

14:12.025 --> 14:13.330
No, no, don't look.

14:13.330 --> 14:14.897
Feel it with your third eye.

14:14.897 --> 14:17.987
I'm sorry, I already looked
with my first two eyes.

14:17.987 --> 14:19.684
He's there.

14:19.684 --> 14:22.209
<i>A guy could tail people
all day hoping one of them</i>

14:22.209 --> 14:23.645
<i>will surprise him.</i>

14:23.645 --> 14:25.603
<i>And by the end
of that day, all he'd have</i>

14:25.603 --> 14:28.389
is a hat full
of disappointment and gum

14:28.389 --> 14:30.652
<i>on the bottom of his shoe.</i>

14:30.652 --> 14:34.264
<i>Oh, gumshoe.
I get it.</i>

14:40.009 --> 14:41.663
Hello, Ben Hawthorne.

14:41.663 --> 14:44.579
<i>Yes, Mr. Hawthorne, I'm
afraid your son Max has caused</i>

14:44.579 --> 14:46.537
<i>quite the problem down
here at school today,</i>

14:46.537 --> 14:48.888
<i>and we need you to
pick him up right away.</i>

14:48.888 --> 14:50.193
Now?

14:50.193 --> 14:52.369
Well, his mom works there.
Can't she do it?

14:52.369 --> 14:54.154
Yes, yes, she is here now.

14:54.154 --> 14:56.025
She says that she
needs you to come, too.

14:56.025 --> 14:58.810
The trouble is so bad, OK?

14:58.810 --> 15:00.725
- OK, I'll be right there.
- Thank you.

15:00.725 --> 15:01.726
Bye-bye.

15:01.726 --> 15:03.946
Yep.

15:13.129 --> 15:15.827
And there he goes.

15:20.702 --> 15:22.660
He's got plenty of room.

15:24.053 --> 15:26.969
- Oh.
- And now he's coming back.

15:26.969 --> 15:28.623
Maybe he forgot something.

15:28.623 --> 15:30.190
It's like he's
pulling away backwards

15:30.190 --> 15:32.932
so he can come in forwards.

15:32.932 --> 15:34.411
This is bad.

15:34.411 --> 15:37.110
Hell, I saw a coked-out
squirrel driving a tricycle

15:37.110 --> 15:39.329
that drive better than that.

15:55.519 --> 15:59.784
You, get me all the alcohol!

