apologize for being late.

19:47.838 --> 19:50.580
Excuse me, is there...

19:50.580 --> 19:53.453
Bullshit.

19:53.453 --> 19:56.412
Dad.

19:56.412 --> 19:57.587
How are you feeling?

19:57.587 --> 19:59.328
I should be the
one apologizing to you

19:59.328 --> 20:02.244
for telling you to live
your life a different way.

20:02.244 --> 20:03.854
This must be some good drugs.

20:03.854 --> 20:06.814
You know, once on TV, in
one of your World Cup races,

20:06.814 --> 20:11.819
they showed what the skier
sees at the top of the hill.

20:11.819 --> 20:13.299
Ah.

20:13.299 --> 20:17.651
Cliff of sheer ice,
and you just drop off it.

20:17.651 --> 20:20.480
Fearless.

20:20.480 --> 20:22.656
Such bravery.

20:24.832 --> 20:28.357
You're my hero.

20:28.357 --> 20:29.924
I'm your hero?

20:29.924 --> 20:33.188
You're everything
that I wasn't in my life.

20:33.188 --> 20:34.972
I had things I wanted to do.

20:34.972 --> 20:37.192
Of course I did.

20:37.192 --> 20:41.414
I took the safe way, no risks.

20:41.414 --> 20:44.243
Not you.

20:44.243 --> 20:49.117
How would you feel if, um,
I didn't have any more races?

20:49.117 --> 20:53.034
Ah, then you'd do
something else great.

20:53.034 --> 20:55.558
I'll meet you at the
bottom of that hill too.

21:10.921 --> 21:12.749
<i>I liked my baby
better when he</i>

21:12.749 --> 21:13.750
<i>was sweet and not so murder-y.</i>

21:13.750 --> 21:15.186
<i>I do not understand.</i>

21:15.186 --> 21:17.754
<i>I gave him a good life,
a freezing-cold planet</i>

21:17.754 --> 21:20.148
<i>to live on where he could
run and play and try</i>

21:20.148 --> 21:21.889
<i>to kill other children.</i>

21:21.889 --> 21:22.977
<i>What does he do?</i>

21:22.977 --> 21:25.458
<i>Tries to stab me with a knife.</i>

21:25.458 --> 21:26.807
<i>The little scamp.</i>

21:28.504 --> 21:30.332
Hello, Harry.

21:30.332 --> 21:31.507
Ah!

21:31.507 --> 21:32.769
Oh, my gosh,
what is wrong with you?

21:32.769 --> 21:34.945
You are not Max's friend.

21:34.945 --> 21:36.599
She was sent away
to girl's prison.

21:36.599 --> 21:37.644
Gifted school.

21:37.644 --> 21:38.819
And I'm back.

21:38.819 --> 21:39.950
How do I know it is you?

21:39.950 --> 21:41.517
How do I know it's you?

21:41.517 --> 21:44.172
Oh, wait, because there
can't be two murdering space

21:44.172 --> 21:46.130
jerks this stupid in one town.

21:46.130 --> 21:47.784
Oh, yes, it is you.

21:47.784 --> 21:49.960
You were not missed.

21:51.353 --> 21:53.224
Why do you have Max's taser?

21:53.224 --> 21:57.272
Because my baby Bridget is
back, and he is acting out.

21:57.272 --> 21:58.273
He's back?

21:58.273 --> 21:59.143
Where?

21:59.143 --> 22:00.449
I missed him so much.

22:00.449 --> 22:01.842
<i>Yes, I forgot.</i>

22:01.842 --> 22:03.539
<i>The baby loves this one.</i>

22:03.539 --> 22:05.236
<i>He will come to her.</i>

22:05.236 --> 22:06.455
Yes.

22:06.455 --> 22:07.978
He misses you, too.

22:07.978 --> 22:10.851
Yeah, talks about
you all the time.

22:10.851 --> 22:14.594
You can soothe
his angry, angry mind.

22:14.594 --> 22:16.291
Let us find him together.

22:16.291 --> 22:19.990
I'll help you,
but only to keep him safe.

22:19.990 --> 22:21.514
I don't trust you.

22:21.514 --> 22:25.300
<i>I will use her as bait,
and she will never know.</i>

22:25.300 --> 22:27.041
You're not gonna
use me as bait.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.651
<i>How does she know
what I'm thinking?</i>

22:28.651 --> 22:30.871
I knew you were thinking that
because you're a simpleton,

22:30.871 --> 22:34.004
and you say the first thought
that enters your stupid head.

22:34.004 --> 22:35.005
<i>I hate her.</i>

22:35.005 --> 22:36.180
I know, you hate me.

22:36.180 --> 22:37.878
♪ La, la, la, la, la, la

22:37.878 --> 22:39.140
♪ I am singing this
song in my head ♪

22:39.140 --> 22:40.794
♪ So she cannot read my mind

22:40.794 --> 22:42.056
That was out loud.

22:42.056 --> 22:43.449
<i>Damn it.</i>

22:52.501 --> 22:56.505
Um, hope a check is OK.

22:56.505 --> 22:58.551
Mm.

23:04.426 --> 23:05.862
Is my dad in here?

23:05.862 --> 23:07.168
Uh, no, that's just my side.

23:07.168 --> 23:09.431
I never was in touch
with his family.

23:09.431 --> 23:10.693
Oh, OK.

23:10.693 --> 23:12.042
Well, maybe you could
tell me who they are,

23:12.042 --> 23:13.392
and then I could go from there.

23:13.392 --> 23:15.263
If you're interested
in things of his,

23:15.263 --> 23:17.700
I have a desk that he left
behind, never got rid of.

23:17.700 --> 23:21.269
Yeah, or you could
just tell me his name.

23:21.269 --> 23:24.794
I could write it down,
put it in the desk.

23:26.709 --> 23:29.146
And sell it to me?

23:29.146 --> 23:30.713
It's a nice desk.

23:36.110 --> 23:37.851
Forget it.

23:37.851 --> 23:39.679
I thought you said you wanted
to know where you came from.

23:39.679 --> 23:41.332
Now I do.

23:41.332 --> 23:43.117
You're better than me,
is that right?

23:43.117 --> 23:44.205
Probably.

23:44.205 --> 23:46.599
Because I gave up a kid?

23:46.599 --> 23:49.645
So did you, as I recall.

23:49.645 --> 23:52.605
Yeah, but I did it for her.

23:52.605 --> 23:55.434
You did it for you.

24:00.439 --> 24:04.051
Coffee's on you.

24:09.796 --> 24:14.104
Oh, I'm sorry.

24:14.104 --> 24:17.281
You know that book,
"Are You My Mother?"

24:17.281 --> 24:19.458
Little baby bird goes
around asking everything

24:19.458 --> 24:22.548
it sees if they're its mother.

24:22.548 --> 24:24.506
I hated that book.

24:24.506 --> 24:29.380
Because, for me,
I knew the answer

24:29.380 --> 24:30.947
was always gonna be no.

24:34.429 --> 24:36.344
And right now, I just want
to tell little me that there

24:36.344 --> 24:38.520
are worse answers than no.

24:41.175 --> 24:42.959
I didn't like
"Winnie the Pooh."

24:44.744 --> 24:47.790
I'm sorry. I just thought
I should say something.

25:05.591 --> 25:06.983
Wait here, deputy.

25:06.983 --> 25:09.812
I'll go talk to the chemist.

25:27.047 --> 25:30.964
Drop it.

25:35.664 --> 25:37.579
Ha-ha-ha.

25:37.579 --> 25:39.450
This the notebook
you're looking for?

25:39.450 --> 25:41.148
Yes.

25:43.411 --> 25:44.717
Wow, that was good.

25:44.717 --> 25:47.676
Your reflexes
seem almost non-human.

25:47.676 --> 25:48.982
I will shoot her.

25:48.982 --> 25:51.201
Drop it.

25:51.201 --> 25:53.116
Drop the gun
or drop the notebook?

25:53.116 --> 25:54.857
The notebook.

25:54.857 --> 25:56.250
Both, actually.

25:58.861 --> 25:59.862
Good.

25:59.862 --> 26:01.429
Kick it over here.

26:01.429 --> 26:03.170
Kick the gun
or kick the notebook?

26:03.170 --> 26:04.563
Both.
Jesus.

26:18.446 --> 26:21.275
Just-- just pick
it up, throw it.

26:27.411 --> 26:29.239
What is the formula for?

26:29.239 --> 26:31.459
Dr. Vanderspeigle
broke it down for us.

26:31.459 --> 26:32.939
If it ends up in
the wrong hands,

26:32.939 --> 26:35.202
it could change how ice
cream is eaten forever.

26:35.202 --> 26:37.421
Fine, don't tell me.

26:37.421 --> 26:39.162
I'll just go in there,
talk to the chemist

26:39.162 --> 26:40.947
myself, get him to
give me some answers.

26:40.947 --> 26:41.948
There is no chemist.

26:41.948 --> 26:43.123
We set you up.

26:43.123 --> 26:44.080
Chemists don't work at night.

26:44.080 --> 26:45.778
Everybody know that.

26:45.778 --> 26:46.953
Everybody does not know that,
because that is not a thing.

26:46.953 --> 26:48.084
You said him.

26:48.084 --> 26:49.303
The chemist could be a her.

26:49.303 --> 26:50.609
That's misogynistic.

26:50.609 --> 26:51.914
You said there
was no chemist.

26:51.914 --> 26:54.047
But if there was.

26:54.047 --> 26:56.919
I can't be misogynistic about
a person that does not exist.

26:56.919 --> 26:58.094
Oh, hell yeah, you can.

26:58.094 --> 26:59.356
The whole world's a landmine.

26:59.356 --> 27:01.576
Well, too bad
there is no chemist.

27:01.576 --> 27:03.839
Because now I'm gonna have
to kill you for no reason.

27:08.191 --> 27:09.410
Get in!

27:09.410 --> 27:11.238
What the hell are you doing?

27:11.238 --> 27:12.674
I'm saving your ass
is what I'm doing.

27:12.674 --> 27:14.110
You could probably
slow down now.

27:14.110 --> 27:15.459
I don't do great
in the back seat.

27:15.459 --> 27:17.070
No way.
He might be following us.

27:17.070 --> 27:18.724
I know half his ass is,
because it's in the bumper.

27:18.724 --> 27:20.551
I think I smell blood
coming through the vent.

27:20.551 --> 27:21.944
Yeah, put it on recirculate.
Do the recirculate.

27:21.944 --> 27:23.337
I don't know where that is.
It's not my car.

27:23.337 --> 27:24.468
- What?
- Whose car is it?

27:24.468 --> 27:25.905
It's Deborah, the town clerk.

27:25.905 --> 27:27.254
You stole Deborah's car?

27:27.254 --> 27:28.908
No I borrowed
her keys after you

27:28.908 --> 27:31.258
tried to ditch me today with
that stupid Russian accent.

27:31.258 --> 27:32.694
You should run it
through a car wash

27:32.694 --> 27:33.739
before you give it back.

27:33.739 --> 27:35.871
Oh, my god!

27:35.871 --> 27:37.873
You made me hire a killer,
and I kill the killer.

27:37.873 --> 27:39.962
And now I'm the killer!
- I didn't do that.

27:39.962 --> 27:41.398
Yes!

27:41.398 --> 27:42.399
No, if you could
pull over for a second

27:42.399 --> 27:43.705
so I can throw up.

27:43.705 --> 27:45.359
Do not throw up
in Deborah's car.

27:45.359 --> 27:46.316
Oh, that's right.

27:46.316 --> 27:47.666
It's not my car.

27:47.666 --> 27:49.102
Now I can pin this on Deborah.
No!

27:49.102 --> 27:50.320
No!

27:50.320 --> 27:51.800
That is not who I am.
Think.

27:51.800 --> 27:52.845
Shit, shit.

27:52.845 --> 27:54.194
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

27:54.194 --> 27:55.369
Maybe he's not dead.
- What?

27:55.369 --> 27:56.805
God, I sure want to be.

27:56.805 --> 27:58.677
No, no, no, no,
we have to go back and see.

27:58.677 --> 28:00.722
There might still be a chance
to clear Deborah's name.

28:00.722 --> 28:03.899
- What? No.
- Hang on.

28:03.899 --> 28:05.466
What the hell?

28:05.466 --> 28:06.946
I think I shit myself.

28:06.946 --> 28:07.990
Oh.

28:07.990 --> 28:10.471
God, it's a regular day.

28:13.387 --> 28:15.302
This is taking too long.

28:15.302 --> 28:17.130
I will make Max come
over and wrestle

28:17.130 --> 28:18.566
you so you can
start sweating and

28:18.566 --> 28:20.524
Bridget can smell your stink.

28:20.524 --> 28:24.441
